name: earlene welton
text: Loved the customer service. Abbey is amazing. Thank you Renegade. This was my first experience, but it won't be my last.

name: Trent Gressett
text: Best summer sausage ever! The jalapeño/cheese smoked sausage has a great taste also but casing is a little big. Haven’t tried the burger yet but heard from others that it’s great too.

name: Cole Rogers
text: Great people with great results

name: Tim Sowell
text: Will not go anywhere else!

name: John Price
text: Very friendly. Great place to get your deer processed

resp.text: Thank you John Price. We appreciate your business

name: Vernon Beaver
text: Took my deer in 6 weeks ago and I have no deer. What did he do with my meat ? I’ve called every week for the last 4 weeks. And he hasn’t called me back about my horns either.

name: Mike Baxter
text: Dropped off my deer on 02-01-20.  Called about every 4 weeks & each time was told "not yet"  Called 03-28-20 & left message.  Mr. Quincy called me back from nursery & said to call Monday 03-30-20.  Called & was told "we'll call you when it's ready".  Last contact, unable to get anyone to answer phone for last couple of weeks.  Today is 04-27-20.

name: Bradyn Peterson
text: Dropped 2 deer off first of January. I have been calling for 6 months. Still no meat processed... Mr. Quincy said it is not his problem he had a lot of deer and had to freeze some. Mr Quincy also owns a nursery and landscaping. Seems like he may have too many irons in the fire. I’m sorry, but this is NOT the type of processing I want. It is the middle of June and still NO meat, he just says I will check and call you Tomm ....same story over and over. He has processed for me in the past and his meat is average at best. Not sure if I will do this again.

name: Jerri Riggins
text: Love any kinda meat that we take here at QUINCY'S.from deer meat to wild hog. The processing is pretty fast, and you get choice of what kinda sets/cuts you ask for.  Prices are more than fair too. If you want friendly, fast, professional wild meats processing done,this is your place👍👍👍👍👍

name: Brandon Stricklin
text: We've been bringing our deer to Quincy's for a few years now and everything is top notch. Everything from the bacon burger to the jalapeno sausage it always delicious. I highly recommend Quincy's for all of your deer processing.

name: Leroy Weather Station
text: Decent prices and quick turnaround

name: John Schortgen
text: Calling multiple times at 10:30 AM and there isn't an answer. Are they only open in the evening?

name: Jason Woodard
text: Highly Recommend!

name: kalyn montague
text: Docking area is tight. Big parking lot across main street to park for days.

name: Trucker Guidance
text: Quick Unload. Overnight parking available off-street. Access prohibited to trucks except from Industrial Blvd from the north. From 431 Go west on Wagner Dr 1.2 miles then south on Industrial .6 miles. Shipping/Receiving is south of W Henderson street on the right.

name: Roy Lentz
text: Great people in shipping aways nice and friendly.  Parking is little tight and the dock doors can be a pain but over all a nice place .

name: Joseph Garrard

text: Got me loaded fairly quick, only 3 hours. Parking lot can be tight. I would come back again.

When called back I was told to never bring anything back to them again. I am 92 years old and  do not feel I was treated with respect and Mr Reed was very rude to me .

name: David Weedon
text: High Quality processor with a vacuum sealed product.  Wide variety of options at competitive pricing.

name: Tomas Wilson
text: I'll be honest, I had some reservations coming from a different part of the country where working with a butcher is handled very different. I let it play out and was very happy with the outcome. Packaging looks great, really happy with the cuts. Both folks I worked with (I imagine the owners) were very nice and great to work with. Definitely plan on using them again. Only thing I would change is on my end that I wished I had a list of everything I wanted to keep ahead of time so I didn't forget things.

name: Geoff Brown
text: Great people. great service

name: Sarah Wood
text: Super nice people my meat looks great! 👍Thanks Reeds processing for doing a good job!

name: Angela Hardee
text: We were notified that our beef was ready and scheduled to pick it up 4 days later so that is would be frozen when we picked it up.     We were disappointed that it was only partially frozen when we picked it up.

name: Pat Mason
text: They always do me a great job. They cut me meat the way I want it.

name: Travis Yarbrough
text: Great people who do good work. We send our cows and pigs to Reed's for processing and have never had a complaint from our customers. Reed and Mrs Loretta have always explained any questions that we have had. The meat yield that we have received from our animals, packaging, and taste have all been wonderful. I would recommend them to anyone. Call ahead of time. They stay busy and that is a testament to their quality.

name: Clayton Hilton
text: Best processor I've ever used, and the only one that makes "hams" out of the hindquarters.  Products are vacuum-packed or wrapped so well that freezer burn is only a problem if you don't eat it within a year. Try their jalapeno & cheddar snack sticks, they are like portable summer sausages.  It doesn't hurt that Reed and Loretta are great people, either.

name: Wb billy
text: Excellent experience. Great people to do business with . They give you a great product-vacuum sealed and keeps very well. I do not know why any one would have  a problem with Reed's . A+

name: Rick Bozeman
text: The best in Alabama

name: Alabama Cowboy
text: Had three pigs that got unloaded this morning very professional easy access and right off the interstate

name: Pat Mason
text: Great quickfreeze. They have processed my meat for years. Call months in advance, as they stay booked. The cuts are exactly as I ordered. I use them Everytime. As long as they are in business, they will have my business.

name: Kim Balzli
text: Meat cuts are great! Carry out service awesome!  Needs help with whom ever may answer the phone, bad customer service on the phone!

name: Kimberly Cole Zemke
text: Beware these meat processors.  We got roped into buying 1/4 of a cow by a relative that pushed until we said yes.  The cow was 1,150 pounds when killed and after processing (removing the head, legs, skin, tail etc... it was 660 pounds and split four ways that is 165 pounds of meat but after these crooks got through stealing the meat from us we only got 103 pounds!!!  NO MATTER HOW YOU SLICE IT THESE FOLKS ARE CROOKS!!!!!  When they were called on it, as we had our meat professionally weighed at another processor and also on our own scales at our shop coming up with 103 pounds both times they told us well we took out the fat and bones, HOW MANY TIMES DO YOU COUNT TAKING OUT THE BONES AND FAT!!!!  Just be honest lady your a crook!!! AVOID THESE FOLKS LIKE THE PLAGUE!!!!!

name: Vikki L
text:
Received 1/2 a cow, cut exactly the way I requested, vacuum sealed, confident I got the meat from the cow I paid for.  Highly recommend Reed's processing.  FYI:  adding more info.  The cow weighed approx. 1400lbs. so my half was 700 pounds.  We got 410lbs of dressed out packaged meat.  this works out to less than $4 per pound and included: stew meat, roasts, rib eyes, NY strip, filet mignon, liver, leg/rib bones for broth and a LOT of 1 pound packs of ground beef which we LOVE!  The flavor is amazing (cow not fed any GMO feed, on grass growing up, hay supplement, finish with non GMO grains (while in a smaller pasture) for 60 or 90 days.

For all you vegans...why are you even at this site?  We don't go to your sites accusing you of killing plants to eat.

name: stephanie
text: GO VEG THEY ARE KILLING BEINGS ITS CALLED MURDER! IF YOU LIKE THAT THEN YOU ARE MESSED UP!

name: Ben Fineburg
text: Rude and couldn't make standard beef cuts that I requested. I will not be using them again.

name: Phillip Driver
text: Best in the business. Enough said!

text: Great prices and great packaging.

name: michael thomas
text: Best custom slaughter around

name: Dianna Delfemine
text: They don't give you all your meat back. We have taken 3 pigs to them and each one we never got everything back we asked for. And what they called bacon you can't slice it up into strips

name: Jimmy Dickinson
text: Honest and reliable.

name: Carrie Kromer
text: Love them

name: Cameron Ellison
text: Used them for 20 plus years, 0 complaints

name: janet williams
text: After getting sick from eating meat from a chain store in the past, I am very cautious about buying meat from just anywhere, and I get very concerned about making any changes in my buying habits. With the recent price hikes in meat prices, I felt it had came time to look for a more reasonable option. I can gladly say I am so glad I founds Gary's Custom Retail Meats. I purchased a good selection of meats, and we have not been disappointed. The hamburger meat is awesome, taste like it doesn't even have any fillers, almost like ground steak! Gary and his wife offer a nice clean store, along with an excellent variety of meat options, and at a lower price than most local stores. The trip to Rainsville is well worth the quality and the price savings. I do not think you will be disappointed! 5+⭐

name: Crystal McClaflin
text: Very poor beef processing. Cuts are look unrecognisable. Gave him several chances. Each time our customers where unhappy with the butchering

name: Bill
text: my wife and I are in flat rock we decided to check out Gary's today. The service there is great ! We picked up some filet mignon  for the grill tonight,they were fantastic ! we picked up other stakes as well as bacon,sausage,and some beets. Based on the quality of the filet's we had tonight Gary's will be are butcher from now on. Thanks for being there Bill&Pam

name: joyce chitwood
text: Great steaks , very nice people

name: Donna Stoker
text:
Great local outlet for fresh meat..also got a butt for the 4th, delish.
Will be returning regularly from now on..

name: Eddie Gifford
text: I've been there 3 times this week and called several times. They are always out of what I'm looking for. Won't be wasting my gas anymore.

name: Wade Bryan
text: Good selection, great service. Weve been using Gary for several years and its as fresh as it gets

name: Chris R
text: Gary has the best meat around locally. Clean fresh environment also.

name: ann west
text: Owners are nice helpful people, the place is clean and pork an beef are always fresh.

name: Brenda Storie
text: Buying several years from Gary's, always a pleasant experience.  Highly recommended

name: Kendall Jordan
text: You can really taste the difference in their meat and the prices are good. I buy all my beef and pork from Gary's.

name: Shannon Arruda
text: This place was great and the owners were an absolute pleasure to meet. We will definitely be going back a lot. Love the fact that the cattle are right there on the premises.

name: Kenny Townsell
text: Fresh as you can get. Good meats.

name: Marlene Trusler
text: Very nice, knowledgeable, and helpful people. Well worth the drive. Thank you for going up and beyond for us.

name: Tammy Spears
text: Nancy and Gary have the best meat around this area

name: Martha Leverett
text: Waiting to cook it and see how good it is.  Prices are good.

name: Gary Holder
text: Great meat, prices,  and polite

name: Supa CG
text: Idk if you guys are actually a 5 star business or not but I live just down the street. I’m less than about 2 miles away, Hence why I chose to give 5 stars

name: Andrea Manley
text: They are great to take your deer to get processed

name: Paul W
text: I  had the bacon burgers from here before. Meat taste was amazing. Tasted great from the sample I had. I was excited to use them. Place was very clean as well. That is where the good stops. You never see anyone there..period..they dont answer the phone ever. And they left a couple of messages for me to pick up my deer...I called several times...NEVER an answer..twice I made the 30 minute drive to pick up said deer..around 3 pm..no one is ever there and they will not answer the phone, so you really dont have a choice but to make the drive out there..30 minutes one way, and hope that they are there. I can not see making a 3rd drive back out there. I lost a deer...they lost a customer that feeds his family on many deer per season. I will stick with Seminole in Phenix City. They always answer and someone is always there. Just got called back. You have to read their sign for pick up hours 4 to 7. I never saw it. Or was told that in my messages.

name: Angel Lamb
text: The guys are very nice. They will unload your deer if they're there if not, you can put in freezer yourself. Jacob was a great help.

name: Jeremy Collins
text: Clean meat, good packaging, fair price

name: Shannon Manley
text: They are the only ones that I know of who makes bacon burger. As  well as  various sausages.

name: Derrick Winfrey
text: First off their prices are high but I was willing to pay because you get what you pay for. Right? Was told 2 weeks when I dropped off my deer, 3 weeks went by and I called and was told it wasn't ready yet that they would call me. Waited 2 more weeks and called back and was told same response. Called the next week and yet again they were so sorry but wasn't ready yet and they would call me. The next week I called and the guy said yeah man it's been done for a while now and we need to get it out we are ready to shut down for the year, so I was heading out of town and was going to stop by before leaving to get it and was told no you can't just show up you have to schedule a pick up time because we have 700 deer in the back and need to find it first. So I had a friend schedule a pick up time and get it for me. When he got it the burger meat was not completely frozen but thought it would be fine. Cooked the first of it last night and the smell wasn't bad and taste was fine, the problem is the amount of deer hair in the meat. Overwhelming amount of hair, like I think they just threw the whole deer in the grinder. I'll process my next deer my self before I take to them.

name: Gene Fulghum
text: I don't really know my first time their to drop off any thing check back with me in a couple of weeks then I can tell you,but as far as friendly service they have that.

name: Ashley Clements
text: Dropped a nice buck off and requested it be caped for a shoulder mount. Said they no longer cape deer. Very disappointed.

resp.text: I’m sorry for the inconvenience, but it is a service we can no longer provide. Most local processors are not accepting whole deer at this time, a service we are still able to provide late in the evening on the weekend. We appreciate your business.

name: Regina Mitchell
text: Everything we have gotten has been terrific!  Great customer service, love the vacuum packing.  Fits nicely in my freezer. Highly recommend

name: Charles Yeager
text: I can always trust these guys to do an awesome job! Great service at a great price! Do not miss out on the jalapeño and cheese summer sausage!

name: Steven Clayton
text: The first thing they did was bring me out the wrong deer head. The other thing was they gave me someone else's deer meat. I know this because I brought them a doe that weighted 56 pounds dressed out and got 40 pounds of meat. Then the next week I brought them my buck that weighted 106 pounds dressed out and only got 42 pounds of meat . they gave me the wrong doe. You're telling me a 106 pound buck only gives you 2 pounds more meat than a 56 pound doe? All he could say was that the doe might have been fatter. If  that was the case wouldn't it have weighted  more? I also have found a lot of hair in the venison burger. I wouldn't recommend this place to anyone!

name: Micah Murphy
text: Quality cuts and highest quality meat packing... Won’t go anywhere else.

name: Jason Edmondson
text: Great people who do quality processing. Best in central Alabama!

name: Randy St John
text: Very courteous. Great processor. Awesome finished product!

name: Douglas Heruska
text: Good customer service however I have eaten five or 6 pounds of the burger and I've had lots of hair in every package! I have never had this issue with any other process until this place.  I will not be using them again

name: Jeffery Denham
text: I've taken several deer here over the years and have never paid over $85 for a deer to be processed. I went to pick up deer meat today and it was $103.99 and this deer had already been gutted unlike all the rest I'd taken there before. Their prices are much higher than any of their competitors and I won't be back.

name: Doug McAnally
text: This is the best deer processors I have every used.

name: Chris Jackson
